Number of children in 5 provinces benefiting from integrated preventive and response services( access to legal aid, social services and expanded diversion and other community-based measures

actual.value: 2015:In 2015, a total of 5,618 children (including 2,488 girls), 2,225 youth and 3,379 families benefited from access to basic and specialized child protection services. Since 2011, more than 35,000 children (including about 14,000 girls) have therefore been reached with services.

title.narrative: Number of children reintegrated from residential care into family-based care

actual.value: 2015:Approximately 361 children have been reunified with their biological parents or placed with their extended family or in foster care. In addition, 194 children (including 152 girls) have been placed in temporary care while waiting for family tracing and reunification.
